verbose_text: However, IL-1 acts through an oxidant- and Akt / Foxo independent mechanism to activate p38 MAPK and stimulate NF-kappaB leading to enhanced expression of MAFbx and MuRF1 and myofibrillar proteolysis in C2C12 myotubes [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: IL-1 acts through an oxidant- and Akt/Foxo-independent mechanism to activate p38 MAPK and stimulate NF-kappaB
